rules: Rule1: If the packing area is ready, then given that neither the desks are allocated nor the relocation is finished, it follows that the inventory is missing.
Rule2: Whenever the packing area is cleared, then under the condition that it is not the case that either the desks are allocated or the relocation is finished, the inventory is missing.
Rule3: If Team A is assigned, then the packing area is ready.
Rule4: Team A is assigned or Team B is assigned.
Rule5: Should Team B be assigned, then the packing area is cleared.
Rule6: In case the facility is inspected, then either the furniture is arranged or either the furniture is unpacked or either the furniture is installed or the relocation is finished.
Rule7: The facility is inspected or the facility is finalized.
Rule8: Either the planning phase is completed or the planning phase is delayed.
Rule9: Under the condition that the facility is finalized, the facility becomes operational.
Rule10: Whenever the facility is operational, it follows that either the furniture is arranged or either the furniture is unpacked or either the furniture is installed or the relocation is finished.
Rule11: The timeline is revised or the timeline is overridden.
Rule12: In case the timeline is overridden, then if the job is paused, the job is delayed.
Rule13: If the planning phase is delayed, then whenever the planning phase is scheduled, the relocation is finished.
Rule14: If the process is documented, then the process is verified.
Rule15: Either the movers are contracted or the movers are rejected.
Rule16: Should the movers be rejected, then if the budget is approved, then whenever the planning phase is completed, then provided that the planning phase is scheduled, the relocation is finished.

Rule17: If the contract is reviewed, then under the condition that it is not the case that if the movers are contracted then if the budget is approved then if the planning phase is completed then if the planning phase is scheduled then the relocation is finished, the issue is escalated.
Rule18: Either the contract is reviewed or the contract is skipped.

Rule19: Whenever the contract is skipped, then given that it is not the case that if the movers are contracted then if the budget is approved then if the planning phase is completed then if the planning phase is scheduled then the relocation is finished, the issue is escalated.
Rule20: Under the condition that it is not the case that either the furniture is installed or the relocation is finished, the furniture is damaged.
Rule21: Provided that it is not the case that if the timeline is revised then the timeline is approved, the deadline is negotiated.
Rule22: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the timeline is revised then the timeline is approved, the deadline is not extended.
Rule23: Should it not be the case that if the deadline is negotiated then the deadline is extended, then the project is penalized.
Rule24: If it is not the case that either the process is disputed or if the process is verified then the dispute is not resolved, then the process is arbitrated.
Rule25: Whenever it is not the case that either the process is disputed or if the process is verified then the dispute is not resolved, then it is not the case that the process is arbitrated.

Rule26: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the movers are contracted then if the budget is approved then if the planning phase is completed then if the planning phase is scheduled then the relocation is finished, the issue is not escalated.
Rule27: If it is not the case that if it is not the case that either the furniture is installed or the relocation is finished then the furniture is not damaged, then the dispute is resolved.
Rule28: Provided that the relocation is not finished, the job is paused.
facts: Fact1: The planning phase is scheduled.
Fact4: It is not the case that the desks are allocated.
Fact5: The inventory is not missing.
Fact6: The furniture is not installed.
Fact7: The furniture is not unpacked.
Fact8: The furniture is not arranged.
Fact9: The job is not delayed.
Fact10: The timeline is not approved.
Fact11: The project is not penalized.
Fact12: The process is not disputed.
